Be secure in who you are and what your values are and you’ll never have a problem blocking out outside noise and opinions. Redefine what success is for you. For me its freedom, waking up each day feeling good about myself. Feeling good about where I am and who I’m with. Genuinely. Other peoples opinions are distractions. They are growth delayers. They are what’s holding you back. As long as your journey feels good to YOU, it doesn’t have to make sense, feel good or seem right for anybody else. Don’t nobody know you better than you!
How you get there? Practice self awareness. Go within. Learn yourself, spend time with YOU. As one of my favorite quotes reads “Knowing yourself is the beginning of ALL wisdom.” 🖤

#DontMindMeImHealing “It gets better” that’s what I’ve learned throughout life. This affirmation has helped me navigate through difficult times. 

Mental health has been a stigma within Black communities and sharing our collective stories and experiences is part of the solution. 

On May 21st, Project Pit, Council member Marqueece Harris-Dawson, the City of Los Angeles, and the California Mental Health Services Authority (CalMHSA) will host the I Love Myself Festival at the Baldwin Hills Crenshaw Mall to help elevate the importance of mental health awareness, advocacy and activity within Black communities. Join community and business leaders, celebrities, influencers and philanthropists on May 21st to celebrate Black healing, communities and culture. Go to @projectpit to learn more about this free event.

Story time: executives used to tell me I can’t sing songs like this cuz I’m black and this was “white ppl music” 🙄 i think one of me and my sisters biggest struggles was being “accepted” as biracial girls and not being put in a box… we were everything! hell, we ARE everything. But according to the music industry we had to “pick a side”.. I used to be so frustrated and we got pulled in so many different directions.. @unclerush wanted us to be urban/hip hop , @la_reid had a different vision and saw us as a mega pop group, I remember when he gave us a song called “anything at all” that sounded just like #backstreetboys and #britneyspears which were booming in that era. Anyways we were pushed into being that R&B group that Russel wanted us to be, had to become “more sexy” and “more black”.. ironically I ended up on #loveandhiphop and that put me even more in that category, now I got millions of followers who like ratchetness while I couldn’t be further from that.. at the end of the day when you’re told who you should be, it never goes well. In my 30’s I started being who I really am I started doing what I really wanted by going indie and life became good. Moral of the story: let ppl be who they are. I’m black! I’m white! I’m pop! I’m R&B! I’m brave! And I’m kind! I AM whatever I wanna be❣️“The privilege of a lifetime is being who you are” remember that 😉 #sarabareilles I love you ! And this song is so relatable thinking of what it was like being signed. #headunderwater

Teaching my children not to feel bad when they say no to something. Teaching them that helping and doing things for others is always a good thing but not at all cost. Are you doing this because you feel obligated and out of fear of being disliked? Or are you doing it because you want to? I struggled with it all my life. And the way it used to affect me is a crazy thing to think about. I still feel bad at times but understanding that putting yourself and your needs first is not selfish but necessary, especially as a mom, was life changing. These days I say no to 80% of things ppl ask me to do for them/with them… because I simply don’t have the capacity.. things become “too much” for me so easily, sleep has become wayyyy too important for me. Free time most definitely does not mean availability! It all comes down to being aware. Aware of yourself, aware of your own needs as a human and aware of your values. I grew up thinking everyone else matters more than me.. I can’t have my kids feel ‘less than’.. ever. No one matters more than you!
Shoutout to our girl Devyn making a cameo in this video (@jean.audri)

7 and a half years (omg sounds so long ago!!) when I decided to pack up and leave New York I was sooooo TORN about that decision. I was so SCARED to start over with a 1 1/2year old and pregnant with my second… no family in America. No “real” friends in LA (besides @_urstruly_inessa❣️) Nothing but blank pages ahead in my book of life with nothing but burning chaos like firework/scribble scrabble pages that were overflowing wit troubled events beforehand💔🖤 I wrote #HappyGirl in 2017 when my kids started bringing me back to LIFE. I owe so much to them. They forced me to put a smile on everyday, go outside and LIVE LIFE.. I don’t know where I would be without my girls @coriandbx they still make me do it. They make me better, also more tired….😅 but most of all: #HAPPIER than ever. I then followed and wrote a whole it of other songs inspired by my daughters. The result, my album entitled #MOtHeR if you don’t have it, check it out I’m very proud of it 🖤
